# Kuranomiya Theme — Cursor Rules

## Project context

WordPress custom theme for a Japanese buy-back (買取) store. Audience: women in their 60s.
Brand concept: 観る (a considered gaze) — restrained, honest, quietly confident. No SWELL.

---

## PHP conventions

- Every function must be prefixed `kuranomiya_` — no exceptions.
- Text domain: `kuranomiya`.
- PHP 8 typed signatures: `function foo(string $x): ?array`.
- `defined('ABSPATH') || exit;` at top of every file in `inc/`.
- Always use `wp_remote_get()` — never `curl_*`.
- Always use `wp_options` for simple storage: `get_option()` / `update_option()` / `delete_option()`.
- JSON-encode option values: `wp_json_encode($data)` / `json_decode($raw, true)`.
- Nonce every admin form: `wp_nonce_field()` + `check_admin_referer()`.
- Sanitise every `$_POST` value with `sanitize_text_field()` before saving.
- Escape every echo in templates: `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()`.
- Never call `wp_redirect()` without `exit` on the next line.

---

## JavaScript conventions

- ES module syntax throughout. No CommonJS (`require`).
- All GSAP logic lives in `assets/js/main.js`. Never instantiate tweens inline in PHP templates.
- Every animation function must guard with `if (prefersReducedMotion) return` at the top.
- GSAP plugins are registered once in `main.js`; do not re-register in other files.
- Import only from `main.js` exports — do not import GSAP directly in other JS files.

---

## Tailwind v4 patterns

- `@import "tailwindcss"` in `main.css` is the only directive. No config file.
- Brand colours and spacing live as CSS custom properties, not Tailwind config extensions.
- Do not use arbitrary values for brand colours (`text-[#B57A3F]` is wrong).
  Define the variable first, then `var(--color-amber)`.
- Never use `!important` overrides — refactor utility order instead.

---

## File structure rules

- PHP templates in theme root: `front-page.php`, `page.php`, `single.php`, `archive.php`, etc.
- Reusable PHP partials in `template-parts/`.
  - Page sections: `template-parts/sections/`
  - UI components: `template-parts/components/`
- Include partials with `get_template_part()`, never `include`/`require`.
- CSS-only rules go in `assets/css/custom.css`. Tailwind utilities go in templates.
- Never add a second Vite entry point without updating `enqueue.php`.

---

## Animation patterns

- Use `data-animate` attributes in HTML; wire them in `main.js` inside `initAnimations()`.

  ```
  data-animate="fade-up"        → fadeInUp(el)
  data-animate="stagger"        → fadeInStagger(el)   (children, x-axis stagger)
  data-animate="stagger-list"   → fadeInStaggerList(el) (children, y-axis stagger)
  data-animate="reveal-left"    → revealFromLeft(el)
  ```

- Hero elements use fixed class names: `.hero-image`, `.hero-title`, `.hero-subtitle`, `.hero-cta`.
  `heroEntrance()` is called automatically when `.hero-image` is present on the page.

- FAQ accordion: mark up as `.faq-list > .faq-item > .faq-question + .faq-answer`.
  `initFAQ()` handles the rest — do not add click handlers manually.

- Header auto-hide: add class `header` or `site-header` to the `<header>` element.
  JS adds/removes `.header--hidden`; CSS in `custom.css` does the slide transition.

- All animations use `start: 'top 85%'` as the ScrollTrigger trigger point.
- Ease conventions: entrances `power2.out`, exits `power2.in`, hero timeline `power2.out`.

---

## WordPress patterns

- Gutenberg is disabled. Never re-enable it. Never suggest WP block patterns here.
- `show_in_rest: false` on all CPTs. The REST API is intentionally not used.
- Vite manifest must be read at runtime — never hardcode hashed filenames from `dist/`.
- Use WP-Cron for scheduled tasks. Register on `after_switch_theme`, clear on `switch_theme`.
- Use `current_time('Y-m-d H:i')` (not `date()`) for WP-aware timestamps.
- Use `wp_schedule_event()` for recurring tasks; `wp_next_scheduled()` to check before scheduling.
- Admin pages go under `add_management_page()` (Tools menu) unless a top-level menu is needed.

---

## Brand tone — for any copy written

- **Do:** warm, measured, considerate, trustworthy, quietly expert, respectful of the customer's story.
- **Don't:** superlatives ("最高", "最安", "業界一"), pressure ("今すぐ", "期間限定"),
  dismissiveness ("簡単", "お気軽に"), or hollow reassurance ("安心してください").
- The customer is likely parting with something meaningful. Write accordingly.
- Required disclaimer on all precious metal price displays:
  「表示価格は店頭での参考買取価格です。実際の査定額は品位や状態により異なります。」

---

## Colour tokens (reference — get exact values from Figma Dev Mode)

```
--color-amber:        #B57A3F  /* CTA / accent — use sparingly (~5% visual weight) */
--color-iron-navy:    #1F2A44  /* dark section backgrounds, footer */
--color-natural-beige:#FAF6EE  /* primary page background */
--color-deep-beige:   #F4EFE4  /* cards, forms, table headers */
--color-ink-black:    #33312D  /* body text */
--color-soft-ink:     #615C56  /* secondary / caption text */
--color-border:       #DED7C7  /* dividers, borders */
```

**Never use `#ffffff` or `#000000`.** Use Natural Beige and Ink Black instead.

