## Layout & spacing (reference — get exact values from Figma Dev Mode)

```
Max content width: 1140–1200px
Grid:              12-column
Gutter:            24px
Container padding: mobile 24–40px / desktop 80–120px

Section gap:       120–160px
Content group gap: 64–80px
Small group gap:   32–48px
Card padding:      24–32px

Breakpoints:
  Mobile:   ≤768px
  Tablet:   769–1024px
  Desktop:  ≥1025px

Touch targets: minimum 44px, recommended 48px
Button padding: vertical 14–16px / horizontal 28–32px
```

---

## Accessibility requirements

- WCAG AA contrast minimum (4.5:1); target AAA (7:1) where possible.
- Never convey information by colour alone.
- All images must have `alt` attributes.
- Form errors: colour + icon + message (not colour alone).
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener"`.
- `prefers-reduced-motion` must be respected everywhere.
